article.headline: Oregon 75, Texas Southern 52
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. -- Tyrone Nared came off the bench to post 13 points and six rebounds as Oregon defeated Texas Southern 75-52 on Tuesday night. The Ducks (4-1) made 60 percent of their shots (15 of 25) in the second half and 52.7 percent for the game. The Tigers (1-4) shot 39.5 percent and committed 21 turnovers, 13 in the first half. E.J. Singler scored 10 points and was the only Ducks starter in double figures, as Oregon's bench outscored Texas Southern's 38-11. Johnathan Loyd and Jay-R Strowbridge led the charge with nine points apiece. Kevin Galloway of the Tigers led all scorers with 18 points, and Lawrence Johnson-Danner added 14, going 6 for 6 from the free throw line. Oregon scored 36 points in the paint to the Tigers' 12.
